 partial money out of their account and taking on a bond that they currently owe
 $900,000.00 and have a remaining 29 years left to pay on it. The bond loans only
 provide a temporary solution for any projects, because it is a simpler way of providing
 funding without putting all the burden on the taxpayers right up front. But in 
actuality, the terms of the bonds end  up costing the taxpayers more in the long
 term. The Town of Bristol still has other projects to be completed but  they must
 find a way of completing the projects without putting the heavy burden on the towns
 people.\tab\par}

